 } } \right| + \left| {\matrix{
   {3{x^2}} &amp; {\cos x} &amp; { - \sin x}  \cr 
   6 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow f''(x) = \left| {\matrix{
   {6x} &amp; { - \sin x} &amp; { - \cos x}  \cr 
   6 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 0  \cr 
   p &amp; {{p^2}} &amp; {{p^3}}  \cr 

 } } \right| + 0 + 0$$<br><br>Since, we have $$f''(0) = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow f''(0) = \left| {\matrix{
   0 &amp; { - \sin 0} &amp; {\cos 0}  \cr 
   6 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 0  \cr 
   p &amp; {{p^2}} &amp; {{p^3}}  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \left| {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1  \cr 
   6 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 0  \cr 
   p &amp; {{p^2}} &amp; {{p^3}}  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 6{p^2} + p = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow p(6p + 1) = 0$$<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ p = 0 or 6p + 1 = 0<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ p = 0 or p = $$ - {1 \over 6}$$ $$\Rightarrow$$ p = $$ - {1 \over 6}$$ or 0

